Follow thb steps below to get a shippable KLone distribution file.

(a) select klone, libu and makl versions and do cvs tagging

(b) create a build directory, say /tmp/klone-<VERSION_X_Y_Z>/ and move there:

    $ mkdir /tmp/klone-<VERSION>/
    $ cd /tmp/klone-<VERSION>/

(c) checkout klone, libu and makl with the chosen version (see step (a))

    $ cvs co -rKLONE_VERSION_X_Y_Z KL/klone KL/libu KL/makl

(d) go to klone root directory and create the needed symlinks to makl and libu:

    $ cd /tmp/klone-<VERSION>/klone
    $ ln -s ../libu
    $ ln -s ../makl

(e) create a minimal Makefile.conf and klone_conf.h via configure:

    $ ./configure -v

(f) create the tbz package, the dist file appears in the working directory and
    is named klone-<VERSION_X_Y_Z>.tbz:

    $ make -f Makefile.dist dist

(g) that's all.


